# Sidebar Width & UX Improvements

## Overview
Optimize sidebar width and improve UX by reducing width by ~25%, removing keyboard shortcut badges, and moving drag handles to the right side.

## Problem Statement
1. **Sidebar too wide** - Text doesn't extend halfway through width (wasted space)
2. **Keyboard shortcuts cluttering UI** - Visual noise from `⌘N`, `⌘P`, `⌘T` badges
3. **Drag handles on left** - Should be on right side for better UX

## Files to Read
- [x] `src/components/Sidebar.tsx` - Main sidebar component
- [x] `src/components/Layout.tsx` - Layout with sidebar margin calculations

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Reduce Sidebar Width by 25%
**File:** `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`
- **Current:** `w-[280px]` (expanded), `w-[60px]` (collapsed)
- **New:** `w-[210px]` (expanded, 25% reduction), `w-[60px]` (collapsed unchanged)
- **Lines to update:** 226

**File:** `src/components/Layout.tsx`
